    "**Patient Education and Lifestyle Counseling:** Provide detailed education on the interplay between stress, anxiety, caffeine, and alcohol with both cardiac symptoms and panic attacks. Advise on stress reduction techniques, regular exercise, and moderation or cessation of caffeine and alcohol intake.",
    "**Consideration of Esophageal Motility Studies/pH Monitoring:** If cardiac and anxiety workup remains negative and chest pain persists as a prominent symptom, further investigation into GERD-related atypical chest pain, possibly with esophageal motility studies or 24-hour pH monitoring, may be warranted to rule out esophageal spasm or severe reflux as a contributing factor."
  ]
}

